e pools for the men's group stage, the U.S. probably had the best draw possible.\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It should be noted that the U.S. finished fourth at the World Cup with a roster of mostly up-and-coming NBA stars, instead of the heavyweights the Americans traditionally send to theOlympics.\", \"from\": 2168, \"to\": 2359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2275, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.134152511233043e-15, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In Group A are Canada, third-place winner at the World Cup with a roster stocked with NBA talent, including MVP hopeful Shai Gilgeous Alexander; Australia, another country with an array of NBA players and then potentially Spain and either Greece or Slovenia.\", \"from\": 2361, \"to\": 2619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2376, \"end\": 2382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9999880273974708, \"rank\": 1.1817214165865278e-05, \"text\": \"Canada\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canada_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2447, \"end\": 2450, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.134152511233043e-15, \"text\": \"NBA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Basketball_Association\"}, {\"begin\": 2469, \"end\": 2472, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBA_Most_Valuable_Player_Award\", \"score\": 0.7056311157095038, \"rank\": 0.3868733798075851, \"tex